                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 813.00/852</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jefferson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-22T10:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Chamorro informed me that he had received a special note from the
                    Honduranean Foreign Office, at the request of President Bertrand, asking him to
                    appoint a plenipotentiary to meet with other Central American representatives in
                    commemoration of September 15 for the purpose of considering the extension of
                    the Central American Court of Justice for another decade but the most important
                    part of the note has to do with Nicaragua joining in the movement for a Central
                    American Union.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
